title: Utah and Stanford on top, Oregon Ducks and Beavers drop; how I voted in the O's Pac-12 Power Rankings
text:
Here is how I voted in The O's Pac-12 Power Rankings poll this (and why).
1. Utah: The conference's only unbeaten team.
2. Stanford: the team to beat in the Pac-12 North
3. Cal: I have to put somebody there.
4. Washington: Big "D," Little "o."
5. USC: Once again playing for an interim coach
6. Arizona State: Starting to put it together.
7. UCLA: Player defections, an arrest, not a good week in Westwood.
8. WSU: Added to Oregon's season of misery
9. Oregon: Vernon Adams to the rescue?
10. Arizona: Took out two weeks of frustration on Oregon State.
11. Colorado: Tough loss in the Valley of the Sun.
12. Oregon State: Debacle in the desert.
-- Ken Goe
